inn1.comm: length ball skidding outside off stump, Watson is away with a languid backfoot steer to third man
back of a length dug in around the off stump, Haddin defends watchfully
the first boundary of the series, backed away outside leg stump, Shafiul gave him some width outside off, and Haddin made good contact with the swing, sending the ball between cover and point
tests out the bounce in the pitch with the short one, doesn't get up much, goes around waist height, Haddin misses out on the pull, and the ball rolls near the crease, Haddin stops it with his bat
stands in the crease, gets more width, and slaps it away for a single to third man
Watson comes forward in his typical defensive push on the off side to a length ball
starts off with a length ball outside off that is carved away by Haddin, but that livewire Shuvo lurks at point, and dives to his right to cut off the boundary
too much width outside off stump, he gets a thick edge down to third man as he looks to drive from the crease
124.8 kph, better line, much closer to off stump, angled in to the batsman, Watson keeps bat and pads close together and defends
more tight stuff from Mash outside off stump, Watson takes a step out and pushes it to covers
Watson looks to use the angle in to him to turn this one through midwicket, but it cut back in sharply to strike him on the body, and rolled away towards Mash
tight line and impeccable length around off that deserves respect, Watson does that with a firm defensive push
hmm, this one kept a bit low outside off stump, Haddin was surprised as he pushed at it from the crease in to the off side

a sign of how this pitch is going to play out as the day goes on, Haddin looked to smash this fuller one down the ground, but was through with the shot early, and had to be satisfied with a single as the ball rolled towards midwicket off the inside edge
Watto with that front foot drive to a delivery that is not quite there for the shot, but it screams off the middle of the bat, and goes on the bounce to mid off
this time he will get the four, full delivery on the pads, and he picks it up with a furious whip of the wrists, and times it so well that it comfortably goes high over the midwicket fielder
a touch late on the forward defensive, but he will pick up a run as the ball goes towards square leg
Haddin is finding out how difficult this pitch is going to get, looked to tee off over extra cover, but the ball came slowly off the surface and he barely managed to clear the infield, mid off fields
backs away outside leg stump, and looking to carve it over point, but Mash keep it around off stump, Haddin manages to guide it past point, and they come back for the second, excellent running

the Narail express is in business, Haddin has perished to that adventurous method of making room outside leg stump, did so again, Mash followed him with a length ball, Haddin had even taken a few steps down the track, had a weak push at it as the ball came in too close, missed, and middle stump is pegged back, it was the slower one
shuffles and defends a length ball off the back foot
a touch uncertain in getting forward, as Ricky is during the start of his innings usually, but manages to push this one in to the off side in the end
stays in the crease and punches a length ball wide of short extra cover
another back foot punch, more power this time, so it goes over short extra cover, but the off side ring is packed and Ricky will have to wait to get off the mark
132.3 kph fuller one targeting the stumps with the angle, Watson gets forward and drives with neat timing to mid on
Australia will have to create their own pace, the pitch isn't giving them anything, Watson looks to belt a length ball but only finds short extra cover
gets some room outside off stump, and throws his bat at it off the front foot, but mistimes the shot in to the ground

that is going to be key on this wicket, he did not go as hard at this one, looked to find the gap at extra cover with the full face of the blade, did precisely that, and picked up three for all that effort
the short ball to Ponting, and you know the response, I will pull them, and then pull some more, Ricky dismisses this one with a savage pull to the midwicket boundary
112.1 kph slower one full outside off, gets Ricky to come forward and drive, goes in the air but fortunately for him, wide of point and away to third man
calmly defended off the back foot towards midwicket
gets on the front foot, waits for an instant for this one to come on around off stump, and guides it towards point

cut away, there were numerous men lurking in that region, but Ricky Ponting gets it through them, he arrested his natural front foot movement, waited for the ball to come on, it wasn't too far outside off, but he timed the shot so well that no one had any chance
and now the perfect straight drive, Mash goes full, too full on the stumps, and Ricky dispatches it past the non-striker, mid on gives up the chase early
and another one, three in three for the great man, stands tall in the crease, and punches a length ball wide of point, third man jogs to the boundary to pick up the ball
he is looking in extremely fine touch, swivels and on-drives, that on-drive, but straight to mid on
fwhipped away off the pads in front of square leg
loud shout for lbw right away, the huge stride down the crease, and looks to defend, but the full delivery strikes him on the pad, not given
fired wide down the leg side
tossed up, this time he does not commit forward fully, stays half forward and drives it towards mid on
goes down on the knee to paddle a fuller one, but short fine leg is in place
drops it a touch short, that is all Ricky needs, even as it went straight on outside leg stump, Ricky backed away even further, and punched it deftly to the left of point, shot of a man in form
played back to the bowler
Watson lunges forward, but the length ball does not come on as well as he would have liked, and his drive goes off the inner half of the bat to mid on
carved off the front foot, some room outside off stump, and Watson smashed it, it wasn't far from point but struck too fiercely for his liking, sped past him even as he put in the dive
clatter, Mash is being belted all around here, this one was full and in Watson's slot, he launched it off the front foot high over mid on, and it just carried over the ropes
goes hard at this one outside off, so hard that there is no timing, and he hits it in to the ground
lots of room outside off stump with the cross seam, Watson looks to bash it off the front foot, and again there is no timing
stays on the back foot and plays a whiplash shot that goes just past the non-striker;s stumps
goes straight on with the arm, he had backed away miles outside leg stump, and missed as he whipped across the line
tossed up around off stump, too full, and Watson takes full toll, goes down on the knee and hammers it over deep midwicket for another maximum
drops it short, gets it to straighten on off stump, but the length is too enticing for Watson, shuffles on the back foot and pulls it to the deep midwicket boundary
now he picks up the single in front of square leg
Ricky comes forward and defends carefully on the off side
fired down the leg side, Ricky gets in to a tangle but no harm done, don't get what this line is achieving
much better, at least he has the chance to get a leg before with this line, straightening on off stump, he goes back and works it in front of square
darted in and turns a touch on middle, played out watchfully on the leg side
another one darted with that slingy action, played out on the leg side, Shuvo has overstepped
down the track shimmies Ricky Ponting, this is the smooth flowing Ponting of vintage, gets to the pitch and lofts it gracefully over long on
wants the single with a tuck to short fine leg, runs a long way down the pitch before Watson sends him back
down on the knee and connects with the sweep to deep square leg
going straight on with the arm and finishing outside leg stump, easily picked away to deep midwicket
with mid on in the circle, Ponting is eyeing that long on boundary, skips down the track, takes it on the full, but cannot beat mid on with the drive
flicked towards square leg for a single
full on leg stump, whipped away on front of square
much better line, what is the need for all this darts outside leg, when you can toss them up a tad on middle,and get the batsman to defend with pad close together
pushed on the leg side, Razzak fields
lunges forward and pushes towards covers for the single
misses the flick, off the pads towards short fine leg
gets way forward and defends earnestly down the track

well, well, you don't see that very often, Ponting is run out by a relay throw from the keeper, he was playing so well, it was swept backward of square, and had almost crossed the ropes but Shafiul running in from deep midwicket just pulled it back inside the ropes, the batsmen realised belatedly it wasn't to be four, and tried to risk the third even as the throw came in to Mushfiqur, Watson had made his ground, but Ricky had been slow to take off for the third, and was well short of his ground even as Rahim relayed the ball to Shuvo who took off the bails
worked away in front of square and that brings the Australia captain on strike
bowled slower through the air, but down the leg side
worked backward of square, direct hit at the non-striker's but Clarke is well home
full on leg stump, and easily worked away through midwicket
leaves the crease, but gets too close to the ball and pushes it on the leg side
shortish to begin with on the pads, whipped through midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, comes forward and defends
again Clarke leaves his crease, Shakib fired it in and Clarke could only push it to midwicket
ooh, this one kept very low, Clarke fortunately managed to get down his bat on it else it was headed for the stumps
drops this one short, and Clarke is waiting, rocks on the back foot and pulls it along the ground to the deep midwicket boundary
punched off the back foot on the off side
too close for the cut, but Watson plays the shot nevertheless, gets it to short third man

Razzak goes up in a fervent and long-drawn appeal, ultimately gets the decision in his favour, Watson was pushing forward, playing for the turn, there hasn't been much of it today, this one went straight on, struck him on the pad, in line with the stumps, would that have missed leg stump, the umpire does not think so, Razzak is delighted
pushed in to the leg side off the front foot
carefully patted away towards midwicket
tossed up on middle stump, White reins himself in and pushes it out to mid off
gets off the mark with a single towards square leg
Clarke wants the single, White doesn't as he pushes one in the air on the leg side, the overthrow fetches them the run in the end
down the track comes Clarke, but is nowhere near the line of the ball, and takes it on the pads
this time he connects with the flick and gets it wide of midwicket
deadbatted resolutely by White off the front foot
much fuller on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
bowled slower through the air outside off stump, pushed away towards covers, White is eager, Clarke is not, Clarke is right
fired in flat on middle, pushed back to the bowler
Clarke uses the feet and picks the single to long on
lunges forward and defends down the track
very tight line this, White defends off he front foot
still flatter, this time outside off, pushed away on the off side
Bangladesh continue to race through the overs, this one loops in the air on the leg side as White pushes hard at it
Clarke continues to operate outside the crease, but finds Shuvo in the way at extra cover
and again, drives from way down the track, but straight to the bowler
leaves the crease again, this one arrives after ages, he stands motionless and then punches it towards covers
on the fourth attempt, he gets the single with a shimmy down the track and a drive to long off
played out off the front foot towards covers
gets forward and defends, no intent at all from White, except the one of obdurate survival
goes back in the crease and takes it off middle stump to cut it to cover

is there a run, now they think there is, now they think there isn't, then they repeat the muddled thought process again, and decide to attempt suicide in the end, Shuvo it is who races in from point and lobs in the underarm throw to Mushfiqur, who is so eager to whip off he bails that he disturbs the stumps before collecting the ball, and Australia fail in the attempt to self-destruct
pushed back down the track

White can't buy a run, can he survive at least, it was tossed up a tad and he wanted to launch it over midwicket, in the form he is in, that was pushing his luck, took it on the pad, bowler thinks that's a goner, but umpire says it's going down leg
does a Clarke, shimmies down the track and takes the single to long on
Clarkes carries on with all that scurrying down the pitch, but pushes this one to mid on
leaves the crease and then tries to dead bat this one, off the pad and loops in the air on the leg side
played out down the track
again he takes it on the pads as he pushes forward
this time he manages to get the single to long on
the shimmy and the single after the bowler fails to field the ball cleanly
languid and calm push off the front foot that beats a diving bowler and earns him a single to long off, brings up the 100
flicked from two steps down the track and wide of midwicket
similar shot, but Clarke is in much better form, times the flick so deftly that it easily beats mid on and runs for four to his right
shout for lbw as he backs away for the cut to a ball on the stumps, not given, was it bat first, or pad first?
played out on the leg side
tentative from the batsman, but he picks up the run as the ball rolls behind point
pushed back to the bowler
punched back to the bowler off the back foot
worked away off the pads through square leg, they want the second, but settle for the single
takes some time to determine what to do with this one on the stumps, and defends it in the end
White has a boundary, he has a boundary, comes down the track, is not too close to the pitch, but nevertheless swings through the line and the ball rolls in to the long on boundary
tries to repeat the shot, this one is much flatter and he pushes on the leg side
pushes this one back to the bowler
goes deep in the crease to work the single to square leg
Shuvo belts out the appeal, he struck the batsman on the pads even as he looked to sweep, struck around off stump, not given, was there some bat?
gets the single this time and gets off strike
hits him on the pads and rolls away down the leg side as he offers no shot
pushed to mid on and they go through for the single, comfortably, in the end
driven down the ground to long off
leaves the crease but is cramped for room and has to push the ball on the leg side
punched to extra cover off the back foot
comes down the track again, but can only push it away towards midwicket
pushed down the track off the front foot
finally, finally he gets the single to long on
punched off the back foot for a run down the ground
slapped away but straight to extra cover
shuffles and whips backward of square leg
White escapes, went for the sweep, has got him on trouble each time, this time he connects and it loops weakly in the air but falls short of fine leg
Clarke goes back and punches a flat delivery to long off
comes down the pitch but gets in to a tangle to defend it on the leg side in the end
this one is much fuller, played out to the bowler
lunges forward and pushes a length ball to extra cover, lots of men in the ring
beaten outside off, went for an aggressive drive from the crease, and missed
shuffles across and plays out this one with the angle to mid on
goes hard at this one full outside off stump, and gets it off the edge to third man
goes for the hook, it was a nasty bouncer, and he managed to get it away in the air towards square leg, and even completed the risky run safely in the end
played back to the bowler, excellent over from Shafiul
pushed off the front foot past the diving bowler and away to long on
Clarke continues to collect runs from way down the track, gets to the pitch and hits this one across the line and gets it in the gap between  midwicket and mid on
he has hardly played from the crease against the spinners, finds mid on this time
this time he drives back to the bowler
angles this on the pads, he skips out and flicks backward of square
sweeps from outside off stump, and gets it to the right of fine leg
calm push down to long on for a single off a length ball
plonks front foot out and gets bat around it to play this one to midwicket
too full and on the pads, flicked stylishly to deep midwicket
this one is outside off stump, and he waits for it to come on and pushes out to extra cover

dropped as they say, straight in, and straight out, even when White manages to middle them, they seem to find the fielders, he swatted the pull straight to midwicket, it went as waist height to him, and he dropped it
pushed out in to the off side
down the track and gets the single to long on
some confusion as White runs halfway down the pitch as this one is pushed to mid on, but makes it back in time
calmly done, takes two steps to the pitch of the ball and hammers it over midwicket
White is in a tearing hurry for the single, again he is halfway down the pitch before being sent back
this time they get the single, worked away backward of square leg
now White leaves the crease but only manages to push out to midwicket
midwicket cuts off the single to his left as Clarke whips a back of a length ball
good short ball, gets big on Clarke, who pulls out of the er, pull in the end
targets the stumps with the length ball, he cannot get the whip past midwicket
115.3 kph slower one, cuts back in outside off, he guides it to point
119.4 kph and keeping low outside off stump, watchfully patted back to the bowler
114.8 kph and very full outside off stump, dug out to extra cover, lovely bowling from Shafiul, first maiden of the game
eased to extra cover off the front foot
now he comes down the track but drives to extra cover again

Imrul puts White out of his misery, he came charging down the track, did not get to the pitch of the ball, and went through with the shot half-heartedly, just managing to chip it in the air, he grimaced right away knowing he was in trouble, Imrul ran in hard from long on, and dived to his right to take a brilliant catch

Clarke lives on, Australia almost could have lost another, went for the single as Shuvo failed to collect the drive cleanly, there was a direct hit at the non-striker's but replays confirm that Clarke was well in
tossed up outside off stump and pushed off the front foot
Mike is away, driving with the turn to long on
whips the shortish one but Shuvo dives and stops the ball at midwicket
eased down the ground with the turn to long on
loops in the air off the pads as he misses on the nudge to midwicket
pushed away towards covers off the front foot
they take on Shuvo with the push to extra cover, direct hit at the striker;s but Clarke was in despite Mike;s horrified look
down the track and driven to the bowler who fails to stop the ball and concedes the run
slung in from a length down the leg side, off the pads and they go swap ends
tight stuff around the off stump, he looks to squirt it wide of point but cannot beat the man
right on the stumps off a length, shuffles and defends off the front foot
spirits out and drives the fuller one confidently but right to extra cover
worked off the pads through square leg, good over from Mash so far
angled in on leg stump from short of a length and turned past midwicket
short ball, he goes back and punches past midwicket to wide of long on
tossed up from round the wicket, defended carefully
clipped off the toes to deep midwicket, goes quickly to the man and they abandon all thoughts of the second run
comes down the track, shoes the full face of the blade and collects a run to long on
cramped for room with one fired straight in and played out to midwicket
Australia continue to attempt those tight singles, this one was cut to cover and Hussey put in the full-length dive but a direct hit and he would have struggled
Mash continues to operate on a tight line around off stump, and he pushes this one down the track
right on the money again, he remains in the crease and gets an inside edge in front of square leg
much fuller this time and he eases it past the non-striker, long on is a bit wide and they jog through for the second, that has to be the most comfortable couple ever taken down the ground
Clarkes gets forward and whips the extra cover drive but mid off runs to his left and cuts it off
pushed away for a single towards mid on this time
another comfortable couple this time off the whip backward of square leg
that one's been worked away through square leg for a single, they thought of a second but Hussey was sent back
slightly short on the off, rocks back and punches it to midwicket
angling in towards middle, worked away towards square leg
cracked off the back foot past extra cover into the deep for a single
tossed up on the off, comes down the track and drives it hard back to the bowler who fumbles and allows them a single
looping in towards off, gets forward and defends it to point
good length on middle, drives it firmly but straight back to the bowler
slightly short outside off, cracked off the back foot wide of deep extra cover for a couple of runs
gets a thick outside edge, tried to push it through the line but it rose up to move away a hint, gets it past a diving point for a single, he's on 49 now
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and punches it to midwicket
slower one bowled short outside off, slaps it past point for a couple of runs, raises his half-century, good start to his stint as full-time captain
gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler, firmly
darted straight in with the angle from round the wicket, turned wide of mid on
continues round the wicket to clarke who flicks through midwicket
goes back in the crease to work this one off the pads behind square leg
tossed up across Clarke from round the wicket, defended off the front foot
length ball staying low on the pads, nudged through square leg
punched off the back foot, Mahmudullah hurries to his right but cannot stop the ball
turned off the back foot in front of square leg
goes straight on with the arm on leg stump, worked away to short fine leg
leaves the crease but is cramped for room, and plays it out to short fine leg in the end
fired in on the pads, that is how you bowl to your field, turned right to short fine leg
lovely bowling, another dot ball, Hussey is forced to play on the leg side with this line from round the stumps
this time he goes deep in the crease to punch a shortish one to long on, end of an excellent over from the captain
turned backward of square leg, Razzak starts off well

short and Clarke will not fail to latch on to those, a fine player of spin is he, rocks back and pulls it over midwicket, wide of the man on the boundary, a four after 63 deliveries says Ranil Abeynaike
pushed back to the bowler
keeps very low on middle stump, he was fortunate to get some bat on it as he went on the back foot
down the track and picks up the single to long on
this time Hussey gets the run down the ground, Razzak cannot stop the ball to his left
gets a leading edge down the track as he looks to whip this one off the pads
Shakib goes down on one knee and appeals, implores, cajoles the umpire, but Hussey was struck about a foot outside off on his failed attempt to sweep
was that off the bat, off the thigh pad, took something as it was darted down the leg side, Mushfiqur could not take it cleanly as he went down on the ground
turned to short fine leg off the back foot, these batting Powerplays I tell you, I just feel for the batting side
eases forward to pick up the single wide of extra cover
leaves the crease and drives the full delivery for the single to long on
this is more like a Powerplay. Clarke comes down the track, makes some room outside leg stump, and lofts with the turn over covers
stays rooted on the crease and nudges wide of short fine leg
this time Hussey leaves the crease but gets too close to the ball, digs it out down the ground in the end
worked away off the hip to short fine leg
easy on the eye, economy of effort, lots of intent, captain Clarke shimmies and eases the ball to long on for the single
rock-solid Mike defends from the crease on the off side
punched down the ground off the back foot
swept away from outside leg stump to deep backward square leg
darted in wide down the leg side, no turn at all
how many times has he done this, leaves the crease and drives down to long on
Mike opens the face at the last instant to run this one outside off wide of Tamim at third man
turned to deep midwicket off the back foot
brings up the 200 with a skip down the track and a flick to short fine leg
tossed up on middle and leg, hustled down the ground to long on
swept down to fine leg for a single
full delivery, flicked wide of long on for a single
guided to point almost from off stump and Clarke hurries across
Clarke takes off, tossed up on leg stump, and he went down on the knee right away, and slogged it over deep midwicket
still fuller this time, turned straight to Shuvo at midwicket
goes for the reverse sweep now, but right to short third man, or short fine leg, or take your pick
pushed in front of covers, another one keeps very low outside off
down the track but pushes straight to the bowler
yet another one does not get up, short and wide, but he could not time the cut because of the low bounce
hurries down the track and gets the single to long off
turned away to square leg for a single
starts off with a wide and full delivery that is squeezed out to point who dives and cuts off the boundary but Mike comes back for the second, what a man
this time he gets the boundary, charges out and looks to go down the ground, off the edge and wide of third man
111 kph slower one on the stumps, stays in the crease and punches it to extra cover

Shafiul gets this one very full and cramps him for room, he digs it out to the bowler, who dives and fields, and then tries a feeble reverse flick of a throw that misses the stumps by about 15 feet, Mushfiqur manages to take the ball
another full delivery, slapped away down the ground
Clarke backs away and swings hard at a short delivery that gets big on him, gets it wide of long on for a couple

Hussey finds long off with precision, got too close to the pitch of the delivery as he skipped down the track, long off had positioned himself nicely under the ball as it came down safely in his hands, big wicket
well, this has been the Australian approach today, play the spinners from down the track, Smith does that and flicks through square leg
scurries down the track and gets the single down the ground
too close for the cut shot, but Smith does so nevertheless, does not get it past point, Clarke wants the single and has to be sent back from midway down the pitch
heave-ho, and clatter, Smith goes for the big one over midwicket, misses the ball that does not turn, and off stump is rattled, Mushfiqur likes it
follow him with a full delivery outside leg stump, he hits it away to midwicket
played out in front of covers off the back foot
played wide of midwicket and they take on Shakib, he goes for the throw at the striker;s end, and misses
103.7 kph slower one, and very full, picked away through midwicket, cannot get much power on the shot
yorker on the stumps, digs it out and gets it wide of Shakib at midwicket who tumbles down as he picks up the ball, and they complete the run
dropped makes some room outside leg and hammers a full and wide one, it flies to point who goes leaping in the air to his left, gets a hand to it, but cannot hold on, tough chance
full and outside off stump, he slaps it down to long off
Mitch with the perfect tee-off pose, front leg out of the way, huge golf swing, even bigger follow through, but the ball barely missed the stumps
slower one and fuller, heaved away to deep midwicket
in the slot outside off stump, Clarke swings it down the ground and picks up two more
and again, this time he moves around in the crease before slamming a fuller one down the ground for a couple more
driven down to long on for a single, and Clarke will keep the strike
Clarke is battering them now, another full delivery hit down to long off
Mitch tries to tee off again, but gets a big inside edge that beats the stumps, beats the keeper, and makes short fine leg give chase
had Shafiul fielded that ball cleanly, Clarke was a goner, he was backing up way down the pitch, Mitch again tried to swing over midwicket but it is not coming on to the bat to his liking
well, what do I know, this time he connects, bends the knee, picks the length ball up, and murders it over deep midwicket
wide full delivery, he missed out on that one, got an edge on the bounce to the keeper
super placement from Mitch, drives neatly wide of extra cover and beats long off too
wide delivery, too wide for Clarke who had to really stretch out to slap that one wide of extra cover, did not get enough power on it, can he get his 100?
poor delivery, low full toss down the pads, and Mitch nudges very delicately, as delicate as Mitch can, and gets it wide of Mushfiqur
attempted yorker turns in to a very low full toss, turned away through midwicket
Michael Clarke, gets the hundred, takes off the helmet, punches the air, it was a short delivery, and he absolutely smoked it over deep midwicket, his team stand up to applaud, lovely innings
now he is gone, got underneath the fuller one and swung it high in the air, long on settled underneath it, and took it tumbling down in the end
waist high full toss to end with, and Mitch kills it over deep square leg, just flicked it off the hip and away she went, the last two overs have cost Bangladesh dear

inn2.comm: 135.7 kph straightens outside off stump, he had already decided to leave it alone, wasn't far from off in the end
length ball comes in and ends up on the pads, clipped away neatly down to fine leg, huge cheers for the run
another one nips back in off the seam, bounces high and hits him on the body as he misses the defensive push
141.9 kph, Lee is cranking it up slowly, digs this one in short, does not get up much but flies past him outside off stump as he weaves out of the way
just over a leaping point, Lee sprayed this one wide outside off, he went hard at it and got it over the man at point
stays in the crease and goes for the drive, beaten as this length ball whizzes past outside off
slung in on the stumps at 137.3 kph, defended carefully
this one zips away after pitching on a length on off stump, he goes back to play it out to covers
looks for the yorker, but it ends up very full on the pads, flicked away through square leg
gets this one on target, and gets it to move away off the seam, he gets back to push to covers
good leave, Mitch is getting them to move away from the left-hander, and he let this one outside off go through to Haddin
137.4 kph yorker zooming in on the stumps, bang on target, he manages to survive, digs it out on the leg side
full delivery around off stump, driven towards mid off
length ball outside off stump, left alone
angles this one in from round the wicket, he gets an inside edge towards midwicket
very full outside off stump, there is a short extra cover in place and it goes straight to him
short and wide outside off stump, he goes for the cut and misses
this one is fuller outside off stump and left alone
Lee gets reward for some good lines, he kept this one full and close to off stump, Kayes had to play at it with that angle from round the stumps, got a fine tickle through to Haddin
slapped away off the back foot, but straight to extra cover
banged in short around off stump, he goes on his toes to fend it down
pushed away in to covers off the front foot
full delivery on the pads, turned away in front of square leg

Mitch gets one now, Nafees had that front foot planted a long way across the stumps, by the times he tried to get the bat around to the full delivery, the ball had already crashed in to pad, Mitch surprisingly went up in an half-hearted appeal, the umpire raised his finger anyways
ends the over with one angling across from back of a length. Defended from the crease to the off side
ka-boom. Tamim's drilled Lee on the up through wide mid off. Corker of a shot, it was a foot and a half outside off, he got half across and slammed it through the line.
better length and line, Lee angles it in closer and holds the length back. Tamim lets it go outside off.
this time he gets too straight, angling into the pads and clipped square for a single.
short ball, lifter outside off and Raqibul gingerly sways away
over-pitched outside off at 140 kph, Raqibul tries to play the square drive, but is a trifle late on the shot. Single to third man.
poor ball, but he gets away with it. Bouncer angling into the hips and it is pulled away well, but straight to short fine leg
pacy offcutter angling across, Raqibul stays on the crease and steers backward of point
Tamim's looking good. Back of a length and not too wide outside off, but Tamim generates tremendous power on the pick-up cover drive. He finds the fielder though.
good response, bouncer like he means it and gunning for Tamim's head. He wisely sways out of the way.
throws his bat at this one, another delivery close to off stump and not there for the drive. Tamim can't heave it away.
fuller ball, swerving into the pads, driven solidly to mid on
this one comes off slower than Tamim expected and he mistimes the off drive to Clarke, trotting to his right at mid off.
tucks him up with pace, Raqibul hangs back in the crease and defends.
fuller this time, Raqibul tries to lean into a cover drive but finds the fielder
aha, inside edge. Cuts in from outside off as he goes for a cover drive and gets the lemon cut away to fine leg.
Tamim slams another four, anything in his half will go, almost like a yard sale. Steps up to the pitch and bashes it over mid on, on the up.
short of length, angled into the hips, Tamim hops onto the back foot and whips to square leg.
Raqibul defends the last ball, back of a length and played back down the track
angling down the leg side and called a wide.
fuller from Mitch, he gets it to curve away nicely and Tamim ends up getting a thick edge on his cover drive, straight to point
neatly done. Mitch sprays a half volley at his ankle, Tamim skips inside the line and clips it backward of square leg
this time he bangs it short of a length and gets it to move away, Tamim looks to crack the cut but finds cover
another one down the leg side. Classic Mitch, this over. Even he can't predict where the next ball will go.
offcutter ends up on the pads and Tamim again clips it through square leg for one.
ah, Raqibul gets some pad on  what would have been a wide down the leg side.
stop the press. The over is over. Offcutter on middle, played carefully into the off side.
angles this one across the batsman from a length, there is lots of room for the cut, but Tamim swings from the crease and is beaten
this time he gets forward neatly and drives delicately to extra cover
fuller from Hastings, he spirits forward to push it wide of Clarke at mid off who has a shy at the stumps and misses
belts a full delivery off the front foot but the gaps seem to have disappeared completely, this time it is mid on who fields
forcing punchy shot off a length ball but again right to extra cover
he drags this one back of a length and Raqibul waits for it to come on and guides it towards point
looks to loft him down the ground in expansive fashion from way outside off stump, gets it off the toe end high over the bowler's head, but it falls inside the circle
that is disdainful and dangerous from Tamim, Watson gave him width and he punched it in the air, just about managing to beat extra cover who leaped in the air but to no avail
and right away, the different angle cramps him for room and he is content to push it away
angles it further in to the batsman, this time short of a length, and he tucks it away to midwicket
Tamim is wiser to this angle now, this one is around off stump, and he makes some room to steer it, but third man is up in the circle and cuts it off
this one nipped back in with the angle, and Tamim took it high on the pad as he missed it, but they steal a leg bye

too close for the cut shot, angled across the batsman but Tamim has a go, misses, Hastings is interested for the caught behind, so is Haddin, the umpire is not convinced, Haddin gives Tamim a mouthful
chopped down to third man
lets the length ball come on to him and pushes it out to point
guided towards point off the back foot
sprayed full and wide dpown the leg side, Haddin misses the take, Lee gives chase at fine leg and almost pulls it back but it trickles on to the ropes
cut away to point, Raqibul is going nowhere at the moment
comes forward for the cover drive, but it rolls away close to the crease off an inside edge
lovely delivery, angles this one on for the drive, Tamim comes out and tries to, but it zips away at the last instant, and beats him
pushed out towards point from the crease
this time he gets one away, poor delivery down the pads and he tickles it past short fine leg, that gets the crowd going again
Watsone sprays this one full on the pads again, lucky not to be dispatched past short fine leg
pushed out to covers off the front foot, better line from Watto
comes down the track for his favourite lofted shot down the ground, but Watson angles it in from a shorter length, and Tamim has to play it out back to Watson who threatens to break the stumps
defended in to the leg side
this is not Raqibul's day, he pings a god looking cover drive, but it goes straight to the fielder, on another day that would have crashed in to the boundary
this one is just around a length outside off, he gets forward hopefully but punches it straight to mid off
this time he gets one away, it was a poorly directed short ball down the leg side and he pulled it on its way to the fine leg boundary

Watto, what a man, goes diving to his left at short extra cover as Raqibul drives in the air away from his body, and comes down on  terra firma with the ball safely lodged in his hands, Raqibul's painful stay is cut short by a blinder, wonderful reflexes from Watson, he just flew to his left, if a big man can do that
shuffles and carefully plays out a length ball bowled from round the stumps towards midwicket
goes slashing hard at a wide one outside off stump, and gets it down to third man off the thick edge
turned away towards square leg
pushed away in to the off side off the back foot
stands in the crease and cuts, but right to point, steady stuff from the bowler
bowled a bit further up around off, and he pushes it to CLarke at mid off
ooh, that was close, Shakib wasn't expecting the fuller one and almost fell over in his attempt to flick it, got it just past midwicket

super shot from Shakib, gets on top of the bounce on this delivery outside off, it cut back in a tad but he was in a lovely position, cut it past a helpless point, and though Lee gave earnest chase from third man, it was too quick for him
shuffles across in the crease and plays out this one to mid on
bit more effort in this one, bounces a bit on Shakib and he shuffles across to defend
fuller this time and on off stump, he drives back to the bowler with the full face of the bat
stays on the back foot and gets in some discomfort as this one cuts back in and keeps low, manages to jam down his bat on it
much fuller and angled in on the pads, flicked away to midwicket
flighted outside off stump, beats him on the drive as it turns in sharply
stays on the back foot and punches back to the bowler
sharp turn even as he backed away for the cut, stayed low too outside off and beat him
fires this one in fuller and strikes him on the pads, going down leg, feels the umpire
good over so far, punched towards extra cover
starts off with a maiden as this one is played out on the off side
flicked away fine down the leg side, poor ball on the pads, and put away
this one did not get up at all, fortunately for Shakib it was outside off stump, had him crouching down as he was beaten by the lack of bounce
shuffles across to flick a fuller one through square leg but cannot time it
plays out a length ball towards midwicket
Hastings goes down the leg side again, and Shakib dabs it very fine past Haddin for another boundary
another one darted in down the leg side, not called a wide, did it take the thigh pad on its way to Haddin, bowler and keeper think there is bat involved, well don't they always?
punched to midwicket off the back foot
full ball swept away to deep square leg
flatter around off stump, turns in and is pushed back to the bowler
turning down the leg side, and Shakib tickles it very late, and Clarke gives chase from slip
goes for the sweep, cannot time it well
tossed up outside off this time, he takes it on the half volley to drive it to extra cover
Tamim fails to get hold of his lofted shot again, hits it high in the air and it falls between mid on and mid off
cut away to point off the back foot
shuffles across, gets outside the line and tucks a short of a length ball through square leg
driven confidently off the front foot, but right back to the bowler
Watson goes shortish on the pads, Tamim hops in the air and works him in front of square
slower one this time, and Shakib mistimes the shot outside off in to the ground
rocks back and cuts it away to deep point
skips down the track and drives this fuller one to long off
tossed up on middle, he lunges forward and plays it with the turn through midwicket
ohh, beaten in flight, he came charging down the track, the ball dipped on him and he was lucky to get an inside edge to short fine leg
shuffles and tucks this one to short fine leg, and is sent back by Tamim after he hurries down for a run
eases this one down the ground to long on
pulls a short ball on one leg through square leg
drags this one a touch shorter outside off, he guides it to point
this one was on a length outside off, and he went down on a knee to slap it past point
another one back of a length, he stands tall and punches it through extra cover
works a length ball wide of White at midwicket who fires in the throw at the non-striker;s but misses, batsman was home anyways
Shakib plays this shot well, shuffles across and tucks a length ball through square leg
down the track and drives off the front foot to long on
worked away with the turn in front of square leg
turns in from middle stump and he tucks it away through square leg
tossed up slowly and turns in sharply on off, watchfully patted back
they pick up a single down to long on as Doherty fails to stop the drive with a dive
beaten for bounce and lack of turn, this one did not spin in much and bounced over his attempted cut outside off
makes a belated decision to steer to Lee at third man
gets it to straighten from around off stump on a length, he stays on the crease and pushes out towards covers
132 kph yorker on the stumps, he stumbles and manages to dig it out to mid on
angled in and strikes him on the pads, he missed the flick as it kept low, Watson is interested, that was clearly missing leg stump
goes right through him, this one too kept low, remained in the crease and wanted to cut it but it went between bat and stumps
good over from Watson, played out to short midwicket
turned off the pads to short fine leg
turns in from outside off and is picked away through square leg
skips down the track and drives with the turn, straight to midwicket
this one skidded on but Shakib had it covered, cut it past short third man for a couple, that will be 3000 runs for Shakib
played out in to the leg side
turning in, punched away to midwicket
stylishly driven off the front foot, pings deep mid off with the shot
Lee goes for the yorker, Tamim manages to jam the bat down on it
140.2 kph delivery that straightens outside off, it is pushed back to him and he throws it back to Haddin, brings the crowd roaring back to life
flicked away through square for a couple
Clarke at mid off is deep, and they take him on with a push, he has a go at the striker's did not hit but made the batsman hurry
called a wide down leg, the Australians think that took something on its way to Haddin
goes for the pull to a short ball that goes big on him, and gets it away to midwicket along the ground
tucked away through square leg for a single
pushed out in to the off side
keeps low  outside off stump, and is cut away through point
eased down the ground to long on for a single
gets a leading edge in the air down to long off as he comes down the track
sharp turn in to the batsman who punches it through midwicket
137.9 kph short delivery and Tamim latches on to it, pulling it wide of midwicket, that will be his half-century as well
fuller delivery, calmly defended down the track
squeezes away a fuller one to point but there is no run available
pacy length ball on middle stump, Lee giving nothing away, defended off the back foot
gets a bit of width outside off now and steers it to third man
this one kept low from short of a length, but he adjusted well, wristing it down to fine leg
tossed up on the stumps, turned away wide of deep midwicket
tossed up very wide of the batsman, who has a go at it and gets it over the off side infield
comes down the track, White shortens the length and gets him to defend they steal a run as the ball rolls on the off side
fuller from White, eased down to long off
turning in down leg stump, swept away backward of square leg
a very ambitious scoop shot, shuffled across the stumps, and picked up a very full ball from around off stump, getting it just over Haddin who ran back furiously
slung in on a length around off stump, defended off the back foot
makes a belated decision to drive this length ball, hits it back in the ground and to Mitch
shatters the non-striker's stumps with the straightest of straight drives, and the ball rolls away towards extra cover
full delivery, lofted in the air down to long on
throws his bat at a fuller delivery on the stumps, and mistimes it towards square leg
driven forcefully off the front foot wide of mid off
goes for the reverse sweep to one around off stump, and takes it on the flap of the pad, on to arm, and on to the ground
after a long time, the crowd get something to cheer about, Tamim goes down on one knee and slogs this full delivery over deep midwicket
tucked away to short fine leg off the back foot
this time Shakib goes for the big shot, is beaten in flight and lofts it in the air but it falls in no man;s land in front of long off
Tamim is gone now, the crowd is silenced, again he looked to go over deep midwicket, but picked out the man in the deep who took a fine tumbling catch
goes on the toes to defend a short of a length ball dug in
goes for the big drive off the front foot but it goes to short extra cover on the bounce
128.2 kph fuller delivery, he tucks it straight to midwicket
misses out on this one, low full toss hit right to short extra cover
125.9 kph full delivery again, he pushes it with the full face past the non-striker;s stumps
banged in short of a length, defended in to the off side
fired in flat and turning in on off stump, played down the track
punched this time down the ground for a single
driven to sweeper cover off the front foot
spirits this one along the ground for a single
defended resolutely off the front foot
swept away to short fine leg
driven down the ground for a single, a trickle here and a drip there, that's how the runs are coming
pushed away towards covers, he wants the single, Shakib is not interested
Smith drops it short, and he backs away to cut it to sweeper cover
punched away to deep midwicket off the back foot
goes for the cut, gets it in the air but it falls well short of short third man
another cut shot, this one was pitched further up, and backward point dives to his left to field
hustles down the track and pushes back to the bowler
turns in sharply, punched to Ponting at midwicket who dives and fields, and then feels his little finger gingerly
short and outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
pushed off the front foot towards covers
pushed out in front of point this time
skips down the track and goes inside out wide of extra cover, long off runs across and fields
driven off the front foot to extra civer
makes room and cuts this one away to backward point
hurries on after pitching around off, stays low too, beats him on the cut
slapped away off the back foot to sweeper cover
rocks back and gets the cut down to deep point
gets forward and plays out this one to midwicket
struck on the pads on the attempted sweep, but outside the line of off
this time he connects with the sweep backward of square leg
down the track spirits Mush, and slaps the drive wide of long off
swept away backward of square leg
pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
this time it is Mush with the sweep on the knee, but there is also a man on the deep midwicket boundary
bowls one short of a length on the pads, he shuffles and picks up a single through square leg
pushed away to extra cover from the crease
wide outside off and dabbed away to third man
rolls away off the pads on the leg side as he misses out on the flick
width outside off, steered away to third man
on the pads, flicked away wide of fine leg
a pleasing on the eye driven single to long off
tossed up outside off stump, Mush drives wide of long off
driven to sweeper cover off the front foot
takes this full toss and sweeps it to fine leg, missed out there
driven down the ground to long off, Bangladesh going through the motions
slapped away down to the ever-busy man at long off
105.6 kph slower one on the stumps, he picks it away to fine leg
dug in from short of a length, defended off the back foot to midwicket
tucked away off the pads, yet another single to fine leg, helps in whittling down the margin, drip by drip
angled back of a length down the pads, tucked away to fine leg
punched off the back foot on the off side
too close for the cut, so he dabs it away, ricky at backward point makes a diving stop, falls over and then almost stands on his head with the momentum
hit away down the ground for a run
driven hard back to the bowler
cut away to deep point off the back foot
Shakib gets to his half-century, tucked away through square leg
looks to hit this one out of the ground, but manages to hit it only to midwicket
lunges forward in defence, but the ball goes between bat and pad but does not roll on to the stumps
gets hit on the pads as he looks to go for a forcing swing over midwicket
slower length delivery, pushed down to mid on for a single
looks to flick this one away in front of square, but misses the ball completely
driven stylishly to mid on, but not much substance to this innings
tucks him up with a fuller one on the stumps, played out in front of midwicket
another one gives him no width, guided towards point off the back foot
Shakib goes now, looking to send this one out of the park, this one did not turn in, went straight on, and settled in the hands of long on easily
tucked away behind square leg
tossed up and smothered off the front foot
smith goes up in appeal but it is turned down, he looked to paddle this one from middle stump,
punched off the back foot down the track
pushed down the track off the front foot
flicks in the air over square leg as Lee bowls one very full on the pads
138 kph reverse swinging full delivery, that he manages to jab away off the inside edge onto boot and on the off side
140.9 kph banged in short and wide down the leg side
goes for an expansive drive through the off side, but chops the ball close to the stumps
118.9 kph slower one tails in from a length, he manages to keep it out
high full toss, surprised Mush who managed to get it away in front of square leg
another one tails in from a fuller length this time, and he stays in the crease to drive wide of Clarke at extra cover
hangs the bat out at a length ball going across him and gets it down to third man
punched in to the off side off the back foot
gets it to cut away off the seam from a length, off a thick edge to third man
tucks this one with the angle backward of square leg for a couple
134.3 kph screamer, too good for everyone, takes the outside edge as it zips away after angling in around off, Haddin got a glove to it but dropped it in the end
fuller this time, pushed down the ground towards mid off
steered in the air wide of third man
short ball dug in down the leg side, he has over stepped
142 kph bouncer fired in, he tried to pull it but was in  no position for the shot
now Lee goes for the yorker, he manages to dig it away wide of midwicket
shortish and wide outside off stump, he dabs it away to third man
misses out on the steer to third man off a widish delivery
backs away outside leg stump and has a big swipe but can't get it past a diving Smith at midwicket
slings this one from round the wicket down the leg side
shuffles, gets outside the line of this one bowled from over the stumps and turns it wide of short fine leg
gets this one off the toe end of the blade and the ball rolls away on the off side
137.9 kph angled across the batsman, he has a poke at it and is beaten
has a go at this fuller one from the crease and is beaten again
a boundary after ages, lovely drive, full delivery and he got it in the gap past short extra cover and beat the man sweeping on the boundary
full and wide outside off stump, squeezed out to Ricky at point
short of a length and turned on the leg side off the back foot
turned through square leg and the man at deep midwicket runs across to field
119 kph length ball around off stump, defended on to the off side
makes room outside leg but Watto follows him, and he has to play it down the track in the end
turned in to the leg side
pulled away in the air to deep midwicket
tossed up and he takes it on, comes down the track and lofts it with the turn to the extra cover boundary
flatter this time and he swings it down to deep midwicket
flighted but dips on Mahmudullah who mistimes the slog down the ground
cut away through point even as it bounces a lot on the batsman
clattered through covers, tossed up ball and he launched in to it, sending it to the extra cover boundary
tucked behind square for a single
straight ball on middle, tucked away through square leg
goes for the cut to a delivery close to off stump, and misses it completely
cramps him for room with a length ball angled in and he tucks it in front of square, direct hit and he was gone
whipped away off the back foot, this one did not rise much but he adjusted well in the end
Mush makes room and mows this one over mid on, just backed away and flat-batted it
goes back in the crease to turn this one in front of midwicket and the way they ran that single with a fervent urgency, you'd believe the chase was still on
tossed up ball, lofted down the ground to long off
stays in the crease and hammers a flighted full delivery to sweeper cover
slogged away to deep midwicket
backs away and cuts this one turning away to sweeper cover
swatted over mid on, it was tossed up and he helped himself to an almighty heave
tossed up delivery played out in front of covers, and that will be the end of this 'chase'
